clickbench-experiments
=======================

This repository contains original tooling (a long-lived "REPL-over-FIFO"
keep-alive harness, per-engine overlay scripts, run drivers, and selftests)
authored to accompany the QuestDB blog post "Lies, Damn Lies and Database
Benchmarks". This original code is licensed under the Apache License 2.0 (see
LICENSE).

It does NOT vendor or redistribute ClickBench.
---------------------------------------------

ClickBench (https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickBench) by Alexey Milovidov and
the ClickHouse team is licensed under the Creative Commons
Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International license
(CC BY-NC-SA 4.0): https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

To respect that license we do not copy ClickBench's scripts, queries, schemas,
or dataset into this repository. Instead, `setup.sh` clones ClickBench from its
canonical source at a pinned commit (see CLICKBENCH_COMMIT), and our overlays
reference the files in that checkout in place.

The benchmark methodology, the 43-query workload, the table schemas, and the
"hits" dataset are the work of the ClickHouse team and remain under
CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. We measure our own numbers with this harness and report them
with attribution, as explicitly anticipated by ClickBench's "Results Usage"
rules. Always reference the original benchmark:
https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickBench/ and https://benchmark.clickhouse.com/

One small exception to "no vendoring": scenario-2-native/modified/duckdb/load
contains the SQL to ingest hits.parquet into the native DuckDB table inside the
resident session. Its int-day/second -> DATE/TIMESTAMP column conversions are
dictated by the dataset and necessarily match those in ClickBench's duckdb/load;
they are reproduced here only as functional glue, with attribution.
